					<div id="about-details" class="details snippet">
						<h1>Hands-on Citizen Science</h1>
<p>Have you ever wished you could  make a difference when you hear about earthquakes or flooding happening on the other side of the world? </p>

<p>Do you want to create a new organism by engineering DNA?</p>  

<p>Maybe do some hardware hacking with I&ntilde;upiat Whale Hunters in the Arctic Circle?</p>
<p><strong>Then you could be a Citizen Scientist.</strong></p>
						
						<p>
Citizen Science is science that anybody can get involved in - gathering field data, analysing and identifying data, playing problem-solving games, and 'hacking' together sensor devices to measure and impact your own direct environment. Even creating and running your own experiments.</p> 
<p>Drop by our workshop and try your hand at being a scientist.
</p>
<p><a href="http://citizencyberlab.eu/portfolio/28-may-2014/">more</a></p>

